{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"86443973-77e6-453b-9aef-485ffd0c6b2a","content":"This is an MTP-enabled MSTest project. To collect crash dumps with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, you need the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` package. Let me add it and run the tests.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_0181vjJRVkPa8exhtwJr49Fb","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /tmp/sv-7e69473395bb41efa58c2879a8ab85ef && dotnet add package Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump 2>&1 | tail -5","description":"Add CrashDump extension package","initial_wait":30},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Add CrashDump extension package"}],"interactionId":"02f8d88e-6765-437e-8ff1-5c168b5f03b5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"This is an MSTest project using Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) since it has `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` set to true. For MTP, the crash dump collection uses `--crashdump` instead of VSTest's `--blame-crash`.\n\nWait, let me think about this more carefully. With `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true`, `dotnet test` acts as a wrapper around MTP. The MTP crash dump option is `--crashdump`, but when using `dotnet test` as the entry point with MTP, you pass MTP options after `--`.\n\nActually, let me reconsider. \n\nWith MSTest 3.8.0 and `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` enabled, this project uses MTP. To pass MTP-specific options through `dotnet test`, I need to use the `--` separator. For crash dump collection, MTP requires the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` package, though the MSTest meta-package starting from v3 may already bundle several MTP extensions including crash dump support.\n\nActually, I need to clarify this - the MSTest SDK includes crash dump by default, but since this project uses `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` directly rather than `MSTest.Sdk`, it won't automatically get the crash dump extension. I'll need to add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` explicitly to the project.\n\nOnce that's in place, I can run `dotnet test -- --crashdump` to enable crash dumps when tests fail.","outputTokens":851,"requestId":"480A:59749:5C13D50:63DC572:69FBEB02"},"id":"16c0b4b2-35e2-4884-b968-2b26508d805e","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:29:56.175Z","parentId":"f701d3a1-8c9a-4a01-a389-94a6a885f45e"}
